  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, since black-box assaults involve less knowledge of the target model than white-box attacks do, protecting against them is typically easier.",
    "Despite significant strides in DL over the past decade, susceptibility to adversarial attacks has persisted.",
    "These attacks can cause neural networks to anticipate things incorrectly because they resemble clean data.",
    "Furthermore, DL models frequently serve as \"black boxes,\" lacking explanations for their outputs, as noted in the study by Perez Tobia et al. [76].",
    "Even though one-pixel attacks are unnoticeable to the human eye, they can have a substantial influence on DNN accuracy."
